"Measures of Engagement A psychometric scale was used to capture the hedonic and cognitive aspects of user experience: the User Engagement Scale (UES) [30]. The UES items pertain to positive and negative aect, users' felt involvement, and focused attention during the task. Aect refers to the emotion mechanisms that inuence our everyday interactions and can act as the primary motivation for sustained engagement [37]. Focused attention [29] refers to the feeling of energised focus and total involvement, often accompanied by loss of awareness of the outside world and distortions in the subjective perception of time. We also tracked cursor activity and gaze" (\href{zotero://open-pdf/0_GCZT4UEG/3}{Arapakis et al 2014:1441})
