"Procedure This was a between-subjects design where participants interacted with the Slide-based or Webcast interface. All participants followed the same experimental procedure: they completed a brief tutorial of the system they were randomly assigned to, and then performed two tasks (presented in counterbalanced order). Participants viewed two presentations, also counterbalanced to prevent order effects. One presentation was on the topic of management and comprised two lectures on leadership and health (total slides: 48; duration: 72 minutes). The other presentation pertained to folksonomies, and culture and heritage (total slides: 46; duration: 57 minutes). Participants completed demographic, two post-task, and a post-session questionnaire. The latter contained the UES with items rated on a 7-point Likert scale ranging from strongly disagree (1) to strongly agree (7)" (\href{zotero://open-pdf/0_TNCTMZEQ/5}{O'Brien-Toms 2010:54})
