"Correlation Analysis An examination of the factor structure of the UES items began with correlation analysis of the items within each of the six sub-scales. As demonstrated in Table 2, most of the sub-scales were significantly correlated with correlation coefficients in the moderate range (0.23 to 0.63). However, the Perceived Usability (PU) showed negative relationships with Novelty (NO) and Focused Attention (FA), a low correlation with Felt Involvement (FI), and a significant relationship with Endurability (EN)" (\href{zotero://open-pdf/0_TNCTMZEQ/6}{O'Brien-Toms 2010:55})
