"Huang (2000) identified two dimensions of information load: novelty and complexity. Huang performed a field experiment in which 115 participants visited shopping web sites with various levels of information load. The results suggested that novelty is important in shaping attitudes as it keeps consumers exploring web sites, whereas complexity results in impulse purchases, encouraging online transactions" (\href{zotero://open-pdf/0_KZLN367W/6}{Soto-Acosta et al 2014:548})
