"Usability theory is a relatively young branch of computer science that has its roots in cognitive psychology (Riva, 2002). Usability is defined as the effectiveness, efficiency, and satisfaction with which specified users achieve specified goals in particular environments (ISO, 1998). It is identified as one of the six characteristics (functionality, reliability, usability, efficiency, maintainability, and portability) of software quality (ISO, 2001)." (\href{zotero://open-pdf/0_KZLN367W/6}{Soto-Acosta et al 2014:548})
