\par
"Following common practice in experimental design, a group discussion was conducted prior to the main study (Hardesty and Bearden, 2004). This was intended to improve the chances that the main study would be adequately designed to comply with the research goal. The group consisted of 20 individuals: ten faculty and ten students. They were all selected because they had experience in the use of the internet and because of their knowledge of marketing research. Moreover the purpose of this group discussion was also to confirm that it was possible to distinguish information overload and information disorganisation in the selected web sites and that this difference was clear enough for research purposes." (\href{zotero://open-pdf/0_KZLN367W/9}{Soto-Acosta et al 2014:551})
